(17087, 654, 'content_1_content_3_dynamic_text_content', '<h4>River Day</h4>\r\nBeginning in 2008, River Day, formerly known as “Snow Day in October” is a day in which the administration approves the cancellation of classes, which is meant to be kept a secret from students, faculty, and staff. This event brings our community together for a day of fun activities and events, and gives people an opportunity to take a pause to enjoy everything happening around them. River Day has been held both in the fall and spring semesters, so you never know when it will happen, but it always seems to come at just the right time when everyone could use a break from the daily routine!'),
