(17121, 654, 'content_1_content_6_dynamic_text_content', '<h4>Gingerbread Competition</h4>\r\nThe Annual Gingerbread Competition is a fun event that allows students to use their creativity to make a structure out of candy and graham crackers. Starting in 2007, this tradition has been kept alive with the generous donations of Goetze Candy and the hard work of faculty and staff on campus. Each year nearly 20 teams of five, or fewer, come together toward the end of the semester to get in the holiday spirit and relieve some stress with this activity. Winning teams receive prizes!'),
