(18111, 48, 'content_1_content_2_dynamic_text_content', '<h3>The Rosamond Page Putnam Center for the Perfoming Arts</h3>\r\nThe Rosamond Page Putnam Center for the Performing Arts is estimated to be a 21,000 square foot state-of-the-art theatre. This new 318 seat performing arts center will establish a permanent legacy, celebrating Mrs. Putnam’s lifelong commitment to the theatre and the arts in New Hampshire. As a new, innovative performing arts venue for the region, the building’s design will accommodate a variety of programming such as dramatic productions, dance and musical performances, political forums and debates, professional lectures, and summer arts programs for K-12 students. Our new facility will provide a 21st century performing arts center serving the needs of the entire campus, while attracting and hosting a variety of arts programming, and providing a center for community arts. The Rosamond Page Putnam Center for the Performing Arts will, first and foremost, stand as a testament to the power of the liberal arts and ensure a vibrant, creative, and intellectual climate for New England College and the local community.'),
