(18147, 48, 'content_1_content_4_dynamic_text_content', '<h3>Planned Giving</h3>\r\nThe H. Raymond Danforth Society was established in the Fall of 1999 to acknowledge and recognize those individuals who have provided for New England College through planned giving.\r\n\r\nH. Raymond Danforth (1958-1969) was the fourth president of New England College. He was steadfast in his determination to gather together the students, faculty, friends, and financial resources that would sustain his vision for New England College as an “international, innovative, student-oriented institution,” competitive with the finest private colleges in the Northeast.\r\n\r\nThat was no small dream, but it is one shared by many alumni/ae and friends of New England College who have ensured our future through a bequest or other planned gift. The College expresses its sincere gratitude for the foresight and generosity of alumni and friends who have joined The H. Raymond Danforth Society by informing the college of their arrangements to include New England College in their estate plans.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5>Common methods od planned giving include</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A gift through a will or living trust</li>\r\n 	<li>Charitable remainder trust</li>\r\n 	<li>Charitable lead trust</li>\r\n 	<li>Retirement account beneficiary</li>\r\n 	<li>Life insurance beneficiary</li>\r\n</ul>'),
